As an examiner, I agree to return the equipment within two (2) days of notice from Pearson. Equipment must be shipped via UPS to Pearson 19500 Bulverde Road, San Antonio, TX 78259, and the equipment must be shipped in the same box that it was received in. Pearson will provide pre-paid shipping labels for me to use for this return shipment.  If I fail to return the equipment to Pearson, I understand that I will be billed for the replacement cost of the equipment.
As an examiner, I understand that I am responsible for any damage to the equipment and are subject to actual replacement costs of any damaged or stolen equipment.

As part of my participation in this project, Pearson will provide me with two (2) Apple® - iPad® with power adapter and connector cable (replacement cost of $975) and a BoxWave Capactitive iPad Stylus (replacement cost of $15).  As an examiner I agree to use this equipment solely for the GFTA-3 Standardization study.  I acknowledge that I am responsible for this equipment and agree to exercise extreme care with this equipment, including securing the equipment whether it's in use or not.

If the equipment is stolen, I will immediately report the theft to Victoria Locke at 210-339-5217 or at victoria.locke@pearson.com and provide her with a copy of the police report documenting the theft of the equipment. Failure to promptly report the theft of the equipment to Pearson and/or providing a police report to Pearson, may result in me being billed for the replacement costs of the equipment.
